<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Minister in Finland (
                        Hamilton
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1947v01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d156</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">156</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1947-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1947-08-13T08:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-08-13T08:00:00-05:00" n="156" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d156">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501 AA/8–1347: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hamilton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-08-13T15:00:00+02:00">August 13, 1947—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>386. It was President’s view and other high officials that Finland’s Peace Treaty
                    should first go into effect and then Finland would apply for UN membership
                        (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 372, August 1<note n="1" xml:id="d156fn1">Not printed.</note>). Finnish Government consequently
                    decided against applying now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hamilton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
